## 🚀 How to Run Locally

### Prerequisites
- Node.js (v18+)
- PostgreSQL installed and running

### 1. Database Setup
Ensure PostgreSQL is running. The backend contains an initialization script that creates all necessary tables (`users`, `tickets`, `partner_assignments`, `ticket_status_log`, etc.).
```bash
cd cctv-backend
# Set your DB credentials in .env
npm run init-db  # If applicable, or let the server auto-init
```

### 2. Start the Backend
```bash
cd cctv-backend
npm install
npm run dev
# Server starts on http://localhost:8080
```

### 3. Start the Frontend
```bash
cd cctv-frontend
npm install
npm run dev
# Client starts on http://localhost:5173
```

